[normal]coordinators raise
[normal] awareness of disability
[normal]-
[normal]related issues.
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]CBM and Mental Health[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]The World Health Organisation (WHO) estimates that 1 in 4 p
[normal]eople will experience an episode of mental illness in their lifetime, and that 300-400 million people worldwide are disabled as a consequence. 85% of these people are in 
[normal]l
[normal]ow and 
[normal]m
[normal]iddle 
[normal]i
[normal]ncome 
[normal]c
[normal]ountries.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]CBM is an active
[normal] member of 
[normal]t
[normal]he Movement for Global Mental Health, 
[normal]and supports
[normal] three call
[normal]s
[normal] for action related to the post-2015 development agenda
[normal] and mental health
[normal]. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Case Study: [bold]A voice for mental health in Sierra Leone[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]In Sierra Leone, mental health needs are especially great as 
[normal]a result of the 1991-2002 civil war that left deep scars on the nation's psychological well-being and its social capital. 
[normal]A whole generation of young people missed out on education, and continues
[normal] to struggle to participate in the economy. 
[normal]People with psychosocial disabilities in
[normal] Sierra Leone are often ostracis
[normal]ed
[normal] from their communities and human rights violations are common. This may be due to traditional beliefs that attribute mental illness to spiritual causes and often blame the person with the problem. A lack of public health awareness and negative attitudes s
[normal]urrounding mental illness has contributed to high levels of stigma and discrimination.  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Existing services consist of a single national psychiatric hospital, which has shortages of staff, medication, and other essential resources, resulting in 
[normal]challenging
[normal] conditions
[normal], including routine chaining of patients. The few civil society services that started after the war are now closed. With no 
[normal]decentralized
[normal] mental health services available through government health services, people must rely on traditional treatm
[normal]ent or travel to the hospital in 
[normal]the capital 
[normal]Freetown.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The Mental Health Coalition of Sierra Leone[bold]&#xa0;[bold]The Mental Health Coalition of Sierra
[normal] Leone was founded in September
[normal] 2010
[normal] with the purpose of creating a body that empowers stakeholders to advocate for t
[normal]heir rights, promoting practical change that will improve quality of life and inclusion in society.
[normal] 
